snippet: At least three people were killed Thursday as Egyptian security forces quashed small, scattered demonstrations by supporters of former President Mohamed Morsi.
abstract: Protests in Egypt leave at least three people dead; supporters of former Pres Mohamed Morsi were observing anniversary of killings of hundreds of protesters in 2013.
lead_paragraph: At least three people were killed Thursday as Egyptian security forces quashed small, scattered demonstrations by supporters of former President Mohamed Morsi.
